
[1]laxative

   LAX'ATIVE, a. [L. laxo.] Having the power or quality of loosening or
   opening the bowels, and relieving from constipation.

   LAX'ATIVE, n. A medicine that relaxes the bowels and relieves from
   costiveness; a gentle purgative.
